comment.author: 54902021@N02
comment._content:
This AC should be ID as follows
Me-262C-1a Swallow JFI(2) w RATO (Rocket Assist Take-off Units)  Ger WWII
Identification
wn Black 130167 (not Marked on AC)
SQ+UF which appears to be a first AC bearing the same wn, and then on to what we see V-167 which more than likely is a second AC bearing WN 130167.
From my experience on this subject, the worke nummer is a constant requiring an AC.
But, in WWII Germany, AC mission(s) in PT (Prototype), Pre Production, & Test Model change were not uncommon and a little out of the norm for AC having (1) wn & a wn being assigned to one (1) AC.
